        <prompt>The ACLU's role in the 1920s focused on:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Economic reforms</option>
            <option letter="b">Defending civil liberties and constitutional rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Supporting prohibition</option>
            <option letter="d">Promoting business interests</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) focused on defending civil liberties and constitutional rights during the 1920s. The organization took on significant cases like the Scopes Trial, defended free speech rights, and challenged government restrictions on personal freedoms. Their work was particularly important during a period of increased government suppression of dissent and restrictions on individual rights.</explanation>
